Push-Ups Training.name: Standard Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Perform a basic push-up with proper form.

Push-Ups Training.name: Diamond Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Place hands close together to target triceps more.

Push-Ups Training.name: Archer Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Extend one arm while pushing with the other.

Push-Ups Training.name: Clapping Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Explosive push-up with a clap at the top.

Push-Ups Training.name: Wide Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Place hands wider than shoulder-width for more chest activation.

Push-Ups Training.name: Close-Grip Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Keep hands directly under your chest to emphasize triceps.

Push-Ups Training.name: Incline Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Perform push-ups with hands on an elevated surface for reduced difficulty.

Push-Ups Training.name: Decline Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Place feet on an elevated surface to increase difficulty and target upper chest.

Push-Ups Training.name: Pseudo Planche Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Lean forward while performing push-ups to increase shoulder and core activation.

Push-Ups Training.name: Hindu Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Move through a full range of motion resembling a dive-bomber movement.

Push-Ups Training.name: Spiderman Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Bring one knee towards the elbow as you lower into a push-up.

Push-Ups Training.name: Pike Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Keep hips elevated and lower yourself to focus on shoulders.

Push-Ups Training.name: Superman Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Explode off the ground and extend arms forward in a Superman position.

Push-Ups Training.name: Typewriter Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Move side to side at the bottom of the push-up to increase lateral strength.

Push-Ups Training.name: Fingertip Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Perform push-ups on your fingertips to strengthen grip and forearm muscles.

Push-Ups Training.name: One-Arm Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Perform push-ups using only one arm for an advanced strength challenge.

Push-Ups Training.name: Explosive Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Push yourself off the ground explosively without clapping.

Push-Ups Training.name: Wall Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Stand against a wall and perform push-ups for an easier variation.

Push-Ups Training.name: Knee Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Perform push-ups with knees on the ground as a beginner-friendly version.

Push-Ups Training.name: Scapular Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Focus on retracting and protracting shoulder blades without bending elbows.

Push-Ups Training.name: Chest Tap Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Push explosively and tap your chest before landing.

Push-Ups Training.name: Behind-the-Back Clap Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Explosive push-up where you clap behind your back.

Push-Ups Training.name: Super Slow Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Lower and push up as slowly as possible to maximize time under tension.

Push-Ups Training.name: Triceps Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Keep elbows tight to your body to target triceps more.

Push-Ups Training.name: Sphinx Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Start in a forearm plank and push up using triceps.

Push-Ups Training.name: Archer Explosive Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Explosive version of the archer push-up where one arm extends further each rep.

Push-Ups Training.name: Dive Bomber Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Start in a pike position, swoop down, and push back up in reverse.

Push-Ups Training.name: Floating Push-Ups
Push-Ups Training.description: Perform a push-up while briefly lifting hands off the ground before descending again.

Push-Ups Training.name: Arm Circles
Push-Ups Training.description: Rotate your arms forward and backward to warm up shoulder joints.

Push-Ups Training.name: Shoulder Shrugs
Push-Ups Training.description: Engage and relax your shoulders to activate stabilizing muscles.

Push-Ups Training.name: Torso Twists
Push-Ups Training.description: Twist your upper body side to side to activate core muscles.

Push-Ups Training.name: Wrist Rolls
Push-Ups Training.description: Rotate your wrists in circles to prepare them for weight-bearing exercises.

Push-Ups Training.name: Chest Openers
Push-Ups Training.description: Stretch your chest by pulling your arms back and squeezing shoulder blades together.
